title: Milestone – 1_12 Ticket Verification (Time to PO 78 – 64 Weeks)
description:
Milestone – 1.12: Ticket Verification (Time to PO: 78 – 64 Weeks)

  • Owner: CVE Site Readiness Lead 
  • Start: 78 weeks before PO
  • Complete: 64 weeks before PO
  • Tracks: PO, VV & HVV

Overview:

The CVE Global Capacity Lead initially creates the project name in the HSD-ES Lab Gen tool based on the official project name from Prognos/Product Roadmap. Subsequently, the CVE Site Readiness Lead for each site creates HSD-ES Readiness tracking tickets using the same tool, with the ETA (Estimated Time of Arrival) based on the projected PO (Power On) date at the time of ticket creation. As the project progresses, the CVE Site Readiness Lead updates the ETA as needed and ensures that the HSD-ES readiness tickets are accurately reflected in the Product Readiness Power BI report and escalate any discrepancies to the CVE Global Capacity Lead. Finally, the CVE Site Readiness Lead assigns ownership of the HSD-ES Lab readiness tracking tickets to the appropriate local contacts, such as CVE Site Asset Managers, CVE Site Infrastructure Leads, CVE Site Lab Managers, or themselves if they are the designated owner.

Tasks:

#

Action

Notes / Examples / Visual Aids

1

CVE Global Capacity Lead creates project name in HSD-ES Lab Gen tool.
  • Name is based off official project name (Prognos/Product roadmap).

2

CVE Site Readiness Lead for each site creates HSD-ES Readiness tracking tickets using HSD-ES Lab Gen tool.
  • ETA for tickets is based off currently projected PO date for project at time of ticket creation.
     ETA date may change as project in in flight – tickets should be updated by CVE Site Readiness Lead accordingly.
  • Please refer to the HSD Lab Gen user manual at HSD Lab Gen Application  (Web view) for details on how to use the HSD-ES Lab Gen tool, including the most recent version of the HSD-ES Lab Gen tool.

3

CVE Site Readiness Lead ensures that HSD-ES Readiness tickets are accurately reflecting on the Product Readiness PowerBI report.
  • If tickets are not reflecting accurately, CVE Site Readiness Lead should escalate to CVE Global Capacity Lead for assistance.

4

The CVE Site Readiness Lead assigns ownership of newly created HSD-ES Lab Readiness tracking tickets to the appropriate local contacts, unless they are the designated owner themselves.
  • Examples of owners: CVE Site Asset Managers, CVE Site Infrastructure Leads, CVE Site Lab Managers, and CVE Site Readiness Lead.

 

Problem / Issue

Cause

Troubleshooting Steps

Issues arise while maintaining tickets or other identified program risk.

All causes.

Escalate to the CVE Global Capacity Lead as needed, using email or instant messaging, for assistance based on the urgency.

HSD-ES Readiness tickets are not accurately reflected on the Product Readiness PowerBI report

All causes.

CVE Site Readiness Lead should escalate to CVE Global Capacity Lead for assistance.

Program not able to be found in Prognos

Mismatched name between CVE/Atlas and Prognos

Confirm with CVE Global Readiness Lead what the correct Prognos name is for a project (may not directly match the name used for other databases/systems)

HSD-ES Lab Gen tool is not creating tickets when tool is run

HSD-ES Lab Gen tool Dependencies folder has not been downloaded alongside the tool

Re-download the entire HSD-ES Lab Gen folder, including the Dependencies folder, and attempt to run the tool again.
 Refer to the HSD-Lab Gen documentation: Installation  (Web view)

title: Milestone – 1.13: Infrastructure Assessment (Time to PO: 78 – 64 Weeks)
description:
Milestone – 1.13: Infrastructure Assessment (Time to PO: 78 – 64 Weeks)

  • Owner: CVE Site Infrastructure Lead and CVE Site Readiness Lead 
  • Start: 78 weeks before PO
  • Complete: 64 weeks before PO 
  • Tracks: PO, VV & HVV

Overview:

The CVE Global Readiness Lead shares high-level technical details of upcoming projects with CVE Site Readiness Leads and CVE Site Infrastructure Leads to estimate basic platform needs for infrastructure analysis. The CVE Site Infrastructure Lead then analyzes the site's ability to support the projected systems, checking power, thermals (PCW), HVAC (cooling), OFA (Oil-Free-Air), and network capabilities. Any risks or gaps identified are reported to the CVE Site Readiness Lead, who then reports program or roadmap risks to the CVE Global Readiness Lead and CVE Global Capacity Lead to determine actions to address or mitigate the issues, such as rebalancing platform counts, relocating platforms, or requesting lab upgrades.

Tasks:

#

Action

Notes / Examples / Visual Aids

5

CVE Global Capacity Lead tracks incoming products and ensures updates are captured in Prognos and the Product Roadmap.
CVE Global Capacity Lead will meet with Verticals and CoE’s to ensure accuracy
Will timely publish any Excel based road map and confirm accuracy of Power BI Roadmap.

6

CVE Global Readiness Lead begins workgroup meetings with CVE Site Readiness Leads to track readiness status and provide updates.
Workgroup meetings should focus on upcoming projects. The priority of each project should reflect its proximity to the PO date, increasing as the project gets closer to this date.

7

CVE Global Readiness Lead obtains high-level technical details of upcoming projects and shares with CVE Site Readiness Leads and CVE Site Infrastructure Leads.
Fine details are not expected this far out from PO – goal is to get best-effort estimations of basic platform needs for infrastructure analysis

8

CVE Site Infrastructure Lead performs analysis of site’s ability to support projected systems, based on provided technical details and quantity of platforms, reporting any identified risks/gaps to CVE Site Readiness Lead

Items to check:

  • Power
  • Thermals/PCW
  • HVAC/Cooling
  • OFA
  • Network (Secure, WiFi, etc.)

9

CVE Site Readiness Lead reports any program/roadmap risks to CVE Global Readiness Lead and CVE Global Capacity Lead to determine courses of action to address/mitigate the identified gap/issue.
Possible resolutions include rebalancing platform counts across sites, relocating existing platforms on site, requesting lab upgrades, etc.

 

Problem / Issue

Cause

Troubleshooting Steps

Issues arise while maintaining tickets or other identified program risk.

All causes.

Escalate to the CVE Global Capacity Lead as needed, using email or instant messaging, for assistance based on the urgency.

HSD-ES Readiness tickets are not accurately reflected on the Product Readiness PowerBI report

All causes.

CVE Site Readiness Lead should escalate to CVE Global Capacity Lead for assistance.

Program not able to be found in Prognos.

Mismatched name between CVE/Atlas and Prognos.

Confirm with CVE Global Readiness Lead what the correct Prognos name is for a project (may not directly match the name used for other databases/systems)

HSD-ES Lab Gen tool is not creating tickets when tool is run.

HSD-ES Lab Gen tool Dependencies folder has not been downloaded alongside the tool.

Re-download the entire HSD-ES Lab Gen folder, including the Dependencies folder, and attempt to run the tool again.
 Refer to the HSD-Lab Gen documentation: Tools BKM  (Web view)

title: Milestone - 2.12: Budgeting Review (Time to PO: 52 – 48 weeks)
description:

The purpose of this section that CVE Site Readiness Lead will start review the WPFW (Who Pays for What) with CVS Budget Owner and Verticals to find gaps in the funding HW & address it accordingly. Any abnormal issue will be escalated to labs global readiness owner.

Task:

#

Action

Notes / Examples / Visual Aids

CVS Labs Management, CVS Budget Owner and Verticals begin to identify Who Pays for What.

 

 
  • Follow budget in Prognos file 1100 with CVS budget owner to check what will be funded by CVS.
  • Reach out to CVS Labs Management and understand about funds/budget.
  • Begin to identify Who Pays for What. 
  • Review with Verticals.
  • Review CVS Budget Owner.
  • Update ticket with result from the review and any after actions.

 

Problem / Issue

Cause

Troubleshooting Steps
Missing HW that is required for PO.

All causes.

CVE Site Readiness Lead escalate to labs global readiness owner 
If missing budget lines (changes ) that not covered in budget 

due product technical changes 

escalate to CVS budget owner for appeal

title: Milestone - 2.13: Platform Loading (Time to PO: 52 – 48 weeks)
description:
Milestone - 2.13: Platform Loading (Time to PO: 52 – 48 weeks)

 

  • Owner: CVE Site Readiness Lead
  • Start: 52 before PO
  • Complete: 48 weeks before PO
  • Tracks: PO, VV & HVV

Overview 

In this section, the CVE Global Readiness Lead and the CVE Site Infrastructure Lead will review products in the roadmap according to Prognos File 4561 (Lab’s platform roadmap). They will use the official product list to define the Plan of Record (PoR) Power On (PO) dates and ensure that the relevant labs have the proper infrastructure to support these POs.

Tasks:

#

Action

Notes / Examples / Visual Aids

11

CVS Readiness Lead tracks incoming products and loads tracking milestones.

 

 

Checkpoint to ensure that Lab Capacity need is understood and has been provided from the Global Readiness Lead. 

 

 

12

CVS Site Infrastructure Lead tracks incoming products

 
  • Compares available infrastructure with requirements and follows up with partners (IT, Corporate Services, etc.) to determine potential solutions.
  • Provide the PO/Main Site Details and Assign Primary TR Lead.
  • Site Lab Technical Lead begins working with Validation Teams to document TR and requirements of the projects. This includes debuggers and other common validation equipment. Inform Verticals long lead items and observed that they are being ordered.
  • Share with the Readiness lead the needs and concerns.

title: Milestone - 2.24: Document Technical Requirements (Time to PO: 50 – 41 weeks)
description:
Milestone - 2.24: Document Technical Requirements (Time to PO: 50 - 41 weeks)


  • Owner: CVE Site Infrastructure Lead
  • Start: 50 weeks before PO
  • Complete: 41 weeks before PO
  • Tracks: PO, VV, HVV

Overview:

CVE Site Infrastructure Lead is responsible for providing a go/no-go decision or defining the requirements to support PO (Power On) and subsequent VV (Volume Validation) in the requested location. This involves verifying that the site can meet various project requirements, including lab facilities (OFA drops, power capacity, HVAC, and PCW adequacy), thermal project requirements (PCW temperature/flow rates and connection requirements), lab network requirements (network capacity, secure and restricted network access), and lab Wi-Fi requirements (network speed and availability for testing). Additionally, CVE Site Infrastructure Lead is to document needs and update the status in Milestone tickets with completion ETAs and create and assign sub-tickets to complete necessary steps, such as adding network ports, PCW drops, and setting up the Wi-Fi network.

Tasks:

#

Action

Notes / Examples / Visual Aids

13

CVE Site Infrastructure Lead verifies that site can meet the lab facilities project requirements.

 

Examples of items to verify are:
 OFA (Oil Free Air) – to ensure that there are enough drops

Power – to ensure that there is adequate power, maintaining no more than 80% utilization of power Capacity
 HVAC - Need to ensure that the HVAC equipment can increased heat from the systems

PCW (Process Chilled Water) has adequate

14

CVE Site Infrastructure Lead verifies that site can meet thermal project requirements.

PCW temperature / flow rates

PCW connection requirements to the Bench/Rack

15

CVE Site Infrastructure Lead verifies that site can meet the lab network requirements.

Network capacity.

Secure Network to all Benches/Racks

Restricted Network to all Benches/Racks

16

Verify that site can meet the lab Wi-Fi requirements.

If Wi-Fi is needed for testing, verify network/speed is available to the lab

17

Document Needs and progress in the ticket comments.

Update status in Milestone tickets along with completion ETA if available.

18

Create any sub tickets need to complete steps above.

Create and assign HSD tickets to PO Roles to add network ports, PCW drops, setup Wi-Fi network etc.

title: Milestone - 3.11: Identify Hardware Needed (Time to PO: 48 - 36 Weeks)

CVE Site Lab Technical Lead informs Verticals about long lead items to ensure timely ordering and shares needs and concerns with the CVE Global Readiness Lead, collaborating on any issues found.

#

Action

Notes / Examples / Visual Aids

Remote Access HW: KVMs, PDUs, USB Power Splitters

Programmers: TTK, Dediprog, USB Blaster

General Use HD/SSD, Chassis & Mechanical Solutions to place systems in lab rack

Lab Hosts: Standard Lab Host Build

Lab Host: Unique hardware requirements

21

Standard Debug Tools: XDP, DCI, BSSB

22

CVE Site Lab Technical Lead Identifies project requirements: T&M Equipment

Needed for calibration scheduling

23

Standard off-the-shelf Cables & Adapters, Rework HW Components (Generalized capacitors, resistors, etc.), Thermal Paste, Thermal Fluid, PPE (as required per EHS)

CVE Site Lab Technical Lead informs Verticals of long lead items and observes that they are being ordered.

TTK3, CTC, Thermal Heads, etc.

25

CVE Site Lab Technical Lead share with the CVE Global Readiness Lead the needs and concerns.

Work with CVE Global Readiness Lead on any issues found.

26

CVE Site Lab Technical Lead engages with the Labs CVE Site Lab Technical Lead

Engage with the CVE Site Lab Technical Lead on any new technology to be defined/developed.

27

CVE Site Lab Technical Lead documents Needs and progress in the ticket comments.

Update status in Milestone tickets along with completion ETA if available.

 

Problem / Issue

Cause

Troubleshooting Steps

Issues arise while maintaining tickets or other identified program risk.

Any cause

Escalate to the CVE Global Readiness Lead as needed, using HSD-ES ticketing system, and email or instant messaging, for assistance based on the urgency.

title: Milestone - 3.21: Procure Hardware Needed (Time to PO: 48 - 36 Weeks)
description:
Milestone - 3.21: Procure Hardware Needed (Time to PO: 48 – 36 Weeks)


  • Owner: CVE Site Readiness Lead
  • Start: WW48
  • Complete: WW36
  • Tracks: PO, VV & HVV

Overview:

The CVE Site Readiness Lead collaborates with the Readiness team to identify site needs and pool lab resources across sites under the "Who Pays for What" framework, working with the local CVE LaAM Asset Manager to assign milestone tickets. The process starts by identifying responsibilities using the relevant document, followed by site audits to verify project requirements against inventories. Engagement and collaboration with CVE Procurement SPoCs, CVE Labs Management, and the CVE LaAM Asset Manager is needed to order additional items, identify active sampling events, and create HSD tickets. All needs and progress are documented in ticket comments, with status updates and completion ETAs in HSD-ES milestone tickets.

Tasks:

#

Action

Notes / Examples / Visual Aids

28

CVE Site Readiness Lead identifies the “Who Pays for What”.
Refer to the Who Pays for What Rev 2 Nov 2022.pptx document.

 

29

CVE Site Readiness Lead perform site Audits of the Project requirement items.
Using project system count numbers extrapolate the total numbers of each item required and verify Site Inventories of each item.

30

Engage with CVE Procurement SPoCs on Reuse
Submit HSD tickets to begin Reuse process to obtain any remaining items not on site

31

Engage with CVE Procurement SPoCs, CVE Labs Management and CVE LaAM Asset Manager for obtaining remaining items.
Identify any active sampling events and Create HSD Tickets to order remaining items.

32

Document Needs and progress in the ticket comments.
Update status in Milestone tickets along with completion ETA if available.

 

Problem / Issue

Cause

Troubleshooting Steps

Procurement issues

Any cause

Escalate to the CVE Procurement SPoCs, CVE Labs Management and CVE LaAM Asset Manager as needed, using HSD-ES ticketing system, and email or instant messaging, for assistance based on the urgency.

title: Milestone - 3.24: Technical Readiness Review (Time to PO: 26 - 16 Weeks)
description:
Milestone - 3.24: Technical Readiness Review (Time to PO: 26 – 16 Weeks)


  • Owner: CVE Site Readiness Lead
  • Start: WW26
  • Complete: WW16
  • Tracks: PO

Overview: 

The CVE Site Readiness Lead is responsible for identifying key players and driving the project forward. This involves confirming needs with the CVE Site Lab Technical Lead by meeting to verify all project requirements. CVE Site Readiness Lead attends Readiness meetings to relay project requirements and any support needed to the Readiness team. They also collect required documents by working with the CVE Site Lab Technical Lead to identify available documents and develop a plan to create or locate any still needed, which may involve creating new HSD tickets and assigning them to the team. Additionally, the Lead reviews milestone tickets and creates any new HSD-ES tickets and assignments needed. All needs and progress are documented in the ticket comments, with status updates provided in milestone tickets along with completion ETAs.

#

Action

Meet with CVE Site Lab Technical Lead and verify all project requirements have been identified.

Relay project requirements and any support needed to team in Pillar meeting.

Work with CVE Site Lab Technical Lead to identify available documents and develop plan to create or locate any still needed. This may require creating new HSD tickets and assigning them to the team.

40

CVE Site Readiness Lead Create New tickets for Team.
Review Milestone tickets and create any new HSD tickets and assignments needed.

41

CVE Site Readiness Lead Document Needs and progress in the ticket comments.
Update status in Milestone tickets along with completion ETA if available.

Cause

Troubleshooting Steps

Ticketing issues

Any cause

title: Milestone - 4.11: - Last Infrastructure Confirmation (Time to PO: 21 – 15 Weeks)
description:
Milestone - 4.11: - Last Infrastructure Confirmation (Time to PO: 21 – 15 Weeks)


  • Owner: CVE Site Infrastructure Lead
  • Start: 21 weeks before PO
  • Complete:15 weeks before PO
  • Tracks: PO, VV & HVV

Overview:

The CVE Site Infrastructure Lead provides last-minute infrastructure evaluation of capabilities for proposed locations. This includes verifying the capacity for thermals (water/chillers), OFA (oil-free air), space, network, and bench location. They also need to ping verticals on the existence of a restricted network and ensure that their software tools are on the whitelist as needed, working with Lab Compute to enable validation. Additionally, they must check on the need for Wi-Fi (Wireless Fidelity) for validation and verify infrastructure at the bench level by walking the space.

Task:

#

Action

Notes / Examples / Visual Aids

42

CVE Site Infrastructure Lead  provides last minute infrastructure capabilities for proposed locations.
  • Need to verify the capacity for Thermals (Water / Chillers), OFA, Space, Network, and bench Location
  • Ping Verticals on the existence of Restricted Network and ensure that their tools are on the whitelist as needed (Work with Lab Compute, to enable validation.)
  • Check on the need for Wi-Fi for validation.
  • Need to verify infrastructure at the bench level (walk the space).

 

Problem / Issue

Cause

Troubleshooting Steps

Identify the vertical to communicate Wi-Fi requirements

All causes.

Escalate to the PO Czar/Lead and/or the VST Lead & CVE LaAM Asset Manager

Identify those to report whitelist requirements to.

All causes.

Escalate to local Lab Compute & CVE LaAM Asset Manager representative.

title: Milestone – 4.12: - Identify Locations (Time to PO: 18 – 15 Weeks)
description:
Milestone – 4.12: - Identify Locations (Time to PO: 18 – 15 Weeks)


  • Owner: CVE Site Readiness Lead
  • Start: 18 weeks before PO
  • Complete: 15 weeks before PO
  • Tracks: PO, VV & HVV

Overview:

The goal is for the CVE Site Readiness Lead to provide detailed information on the platforms needed from PO (Power On) through HVV (High Volume Validation). This information is crucial for planning the target location for the activities (PO through HVV) according to each business unit. The process involves working directly with the PO Czar/Lead to gather and understand the verticals' needs. The collected requirements are subsequently presented in the Readiness forums, where any gaps or issues are addressed and resolved.

Task:

#

Action

Notes / Examples / Visual Aids

43

The goal is for the CVE Site Readiness Lead to provide information on the requirements for platforms needed for PO through HVV. This information will be used in planning the target location for the activities according to each business unit.
  • Query the information from the PO Czar/Lead and understand the verticals needs.     Report the requirements to the within the Readiness forums and drive gaps/issues to resolution.

Note: This information will be needed in Milestone 4.21.

title: Milestone – 4.14: - Management Review (Time to PO: 18 – 11 Weeks)
description:
Milestone – 4.14: - Management Review (Time to PO: 18 – 11 Weeks)


  • Owner: CVE Site Readiness Lead
  • Start: 18 weeks before PO

Overview:

Management Review involves CVE Site Readiness Lead and the CVE Site Manager approving the final landing zone for incoming platforms. The process is considered complete once the CVE Site Manager has given their approval for the designated landing zone, ensuring that all necessary preparations and alignments with verticals are in place for the incoming platforms.

Tasks:

#

Action

Notes / Examples / Visual Aids

44

CVE Site Readiness Lead and the CVE Site Manager has approved the final landing zone for incoming platforms.

 
  • Completion is when, Site Manager has approved the final landing zone for incoming platforms.

 

 

Problem / Issue

Cause

Troubleshooting Steps

Landing zone is not clear.

All causes.

Work with local CVE Local Lab Lead to ensure that space is available for PO.

title: Milestone – 4.21: - Confirm Capacity (Time to PO: 16 – 13 Weeks)
description:
Milestone – 4.21: - Confirm Capacity (Time to PO: 16 – 13 Weeks)


  • Owner: CVE Site Readiness Lead
  • Start: 16 weeks before PO
  • Complete: 13 weeks before PO
  • Tracks: PO, VV & HVV

Overview:

Confirming capacity involves the CVE Site Readiness Lead collaborating with Verticals including PO (Power On) Lead and VST (Validation Steering Team) to determine the approximate number of systems needed from PO through HVV (High Volume Validation) for layout and space planning. This information, derived from Milestone 4.12, is then reviewed and presented to the CVE Local Site Manager for approval. The process also includes accounting for debuggers and other common validation equipment to ensure comprehensive planning and resource allocation.

Task:

#

Action

Notes / Examples / Visual Aids

45

CVE Site Readiness Lead works with Verticals (PO Lead / VST) to understand the approximate number of systems for PO through to HVV needed for layout/space planning and present to CVE Local Site Manager.

 
Take the information from Milestone 4.12 and review with the CVE Local Site Manager.


 Note: Remember to include debuggers and other common validation equipment for assignment.

 

Problem / Issue

Cause

Troubleshooting Steps

If you do not get approximate number of platforms at this stage

Lack of communication

CVE Site Readiness Lad should reach out to CVE Global Readiness Lead for assistance

title: Milestone - 5.11: Verify Hardware and T&M (Time to PO: 16-10 weeks)
description:
Milestone - 5.11: Verify Hardware and T&M (Time to PO: 16-10 weeks)


  • Owner: CVE Site Infrastructure Lead
  • Start: 16 weeks before PO
  • Complete: 10 weeks before PO
  • Tracks: PO

Overview:

CVE Site Readiness Lead to identify and procure any remaining hardware needs, particularly test and measurement equipment, to ensure no gaps or blocks exist for the power-on process. description:

  • Owner: CVE Site Readiness Lead
  • Start: Beginning of PO
  • Complete: 4 weeks after PO
  • Tracks: VV

Overview:

CVE Lab Site Readiness Lead is responsible for monitoring the PO and transitioning into volume validation. This involves working closely with vertical and CVE Labs Management to ensure a smooth transition to volume validation and sustaining mode. Key actions include identifying the point of contact PoC (Point of Contact) for the vertical, sharing and aligning transition plans with all stakeholders, and working with labs to create tickets to initiate the transition plan to validation. Additionally, any issues that arise should be escalated to management as needed.

Task:

#

Action

  2. Share with the transition plans and ensure that they are in alignment with it.
  3. Work with labs to ensure that tickets are being created to initiate the transition plan to validation.
  4. Escalate any issue to management(s).

 

Problem / Issue

Cause

Troubleshooting Steps

Lack of communication by verticals

All causes.

Escalate to the CVE Labs Management as needed, for assistance based on the urgency.
